==Finnish==
===Etymology===
A borrowing of Germanic *''kuningaz''. As Finnish seems to be a very conservative language (i.e., it usually retains the basic structure of the language it had borrowed from), the Finnish word shows how a masculine noun looked like in the (Proto-) Germanic language.
